snippet: Malaysian security forces battled on Friday morning with about 180 Filipinos in an effort to remove them from a remote coastal village, leaving at least 13 people dead.
abstract: Malaysian security forces battle with about 180 Filipinos in an effort to remove them from a remote coastal village, leaving at least 13 people dead; conflict erupts from an obscure, centuries-old territorial dispute between Malaysia and the Philippines

byline.contributor: Floyd Whaley reported from Manila, and Gerry Mullany from Hong Kong.

lead_paragraph: Malaysian security forces battled on Friday morning with about 180 Filipinos in an effort to remove them from a remote coastal village, leaving at least 13 people dead.

headline.seo: Malaysian Incursion by Filipinos Ends in Deadly Clash
